t fade in the middle of it...<br><br>But I like change. I've been to the following over the course of this level, trying experience: CoM (slightly better than SolB, but out of the way), EJ (*smirks* I think I was drunk), DL (zzz..), SolB (death trap), CC (dark blues are perma-camped..), EW (so-so.. less banter in EW than DL.. sometimes), GD (Giants are alright, but I have to fear kite..) and probably a few more places I don't remember. These were all solo, mind you. Grouped I've been to Skyfire, SolB (much better than solo), and a few other random places. With a small, decent group in SolB, experience is awesome.<br><br>Now, granted I am getting a chance to, at times, group with members of my guild (51 Monk, 50 Cleric, 53 Enchanter) and I have also partnered with a 51 Shaman in DL which was nice, I'd like to know first off, where should we as a group go? (I'm too young for OS by the way, and neither of us monks have our key - the enchanter refuses to go to KC - we've all had enough of LGuk for about a century) All members of said party are moderately equipped and work well together.<br><br>For times when I do not have the resources for a group (pickup groups irk me nowadays...) and/or wish to solo, where could I go? Don't have an EB item, so Bloodgills are not really an option. Iksar monk, as you guessed by the name, I'm sure, so keep in mind some faction issues on Luclin (those which prevent me from going to Scarlet Desert *sighs* which I would really like to try). Anyway, 48 Monk, equipment posted in Magelo (Though upgraded with about 100 more hp and  4 less AC), asking for places to try my hand at soloing.<br><br>Also, on the issue of Mend and soloing. I've been waiting until Mend was absolutely necessary to press it, mainly because I am a stubborn person and try to win the fight without Mend to conserve it. Should I just hit it below 75% always when soloing?<br> <p><div align="center">  <table border="0" width="361" height="191">    <tr>      <td