ned to use it as soon as it pops to boost my heal (and therefore exp) rate.<br><br>All depends how much damage you're taking and how frequently you get in difficulties.<br><br>Just my personal opinion, but I hope it helps <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kiroc>Kiroc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 220<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/13/02 4:17:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1773.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> My Mend Take...</span><hr size=1> Unless I'm getting my arse whupped constantly (in which case, I'm fighting the wrong mobs) I use Mend as soon as I hit 75%.<br><br>Why?<br><br>1. Mob Running<br>Mobs usually try to flee on about their last bubble of health.  If you're on the same level of health, they're less likely to in my experience.<br><br>2. Timing<br>Using it at the start of a fight means you set the &quot;re-pop&quot; timer off earlier.  In other words, Mend becomes available in 6 minutes from that point, rather than 6 minutes from the end of the fight.<br><br>That's my take on it and I seem to have some success with it, but in the end it's down to personal play tactics.<br><br><br>- Kiroc <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucurscale.showPublicProfile?language=EN>curscale</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master</span><br>  Posts: 516<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/13/02 11:51:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1773.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://thumb-1.image.altavista.com/image/15837144 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My Mend Take...</span><hr size=1> Start camping the Taskmaster in Echo with your friends. once you get three guts, get an amulet of the grey wastes from Katta. Voila! easy bloodgills now, good luck! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uglaydor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glaydor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 97<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/15/02 6:31:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1773.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My Mend Take...</span><hr size=1> With the new ports you should have no problem getting to scarlett. not sure if ikkys are kos in TS though. The stuff in SD are great xp and seem to fear easily. Havent soloed there, but was grouping there. Just me a chanter and a SK. we were fearkiting. Is your chanter a DE? Chances are they dont want to mess up their VS faction in KC which kills your faction in the OT outpost. And I know wizard wise there are spells that can only be bought in either FV or OT outposts, so it might be the same for chanters.  Can &quot;Try&quot; fearkiting seafuries in OOT. but too many add chances. Echo is probably your best bet. doing underbulks (do not do fireclaw solo, he was eating me alive at 52 solo between firedamage and melee hits) and fungoinds. To do taskmaster and skeles you'll need a healer or some type of backup. Taskmaster is soloable by 51 and you cant pull the skeletons without pulling the taskmaster (but you can pull the taskmaster without skeleton adds) <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=220310">Glaydor's Gear</a> Glaydor Level 52 Disciple Agnostic on the Terris Thule Server</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usscalecladssaberclaws.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sscaleclad Ssaberclaws</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 100<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/15/02 5:09:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1773.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My Mend Take...</span><hr size=1> <br>Thank you for the advice everyone. I will take a closer look at Echo and also at SD with the new ports. (Ported into TS the other day but the lag was too bad for me to move much)<br><br>And yes, the chanter is a dark elf and doesn't want to ruin his faction at the outpost. <p><div align="center">  <table border="0" width="361" height="191">    <tr>      <td width="104" height="191"><img src="http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/Sscaleclad/fullsize/scalecabsig.jpg" width="114" height="190"></td>      <td width="241" height="191" valign="middle" align="left">        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><b><i><font size="3"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=294029">Sscaleclad Ssaberclaws</a></font></i></b></p>        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">Swifttail of        the 48th Season</p>        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">Proud        Officer of <a href="http://pub66.ezboard.com/bnorrathseliteguard">Norrath's        Elite Guard</a></p>        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"> </p>        <br><p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><i>"I don't need to kill anyone just to prove that I am strong. I use my skill to protect the people I